    "body": "## Summary\n\nGEMM v2 has been the default path for a while and no tests or examples still depend on v1. This PR removes the legacy C++ `GemmNode` / `tl_gemm` builtin path entirely and promotes the former `GemmPyNode` (Python-delegated lowering) to be the one and only GEMM tile op, collapsing the two parallel implementations into one.\n\n## Changes\n\n### C++\n- Merge `src/op/gemm_py.{h,cc}` into `src/op/gemm.{h,cc}`: `GemmPyNode` → `GemmNode`, `GemmPy` → `Gemm`, FFI type key `tl.GemmPy` → `tl.Gemm`, op names `tl.tileop.{gemm_py, wgmma_gemm_py, tcgen05_gemm_py}` → `tl.tileop.{gemm, wgmma_gemm, tcgen05_gemm}`.\n- Shared infrastructure (`GemmWarpPolicyNode`, `GemmInst` enum, `GemmWarpPolicyNode::computeWarpPartition`) stays in place so `GemmSP` / `GemmSPPy` keep compiling unchanged.\n- Delete the `tl_gemm` builtin, its codegen dispatch in `codegen_{cuda,hip,cutedsl}.cc`, and its matching branches in `inject_fence_proxy.cc` and `merge_shared_memory_allocations.cc`. `tl_gemm_sp` is kept as the remaining async-proxy gemm builtin.\n- Drop `#include \"\"gemm_py.h\"\"` and `GemmPyNode` / `GemmPy` references from `inject_pipeline.cc`, `producer_consumer_ws.cc`, and `lower_blackwell_2sm.cc`.\n\n### Python\n- `tilelang/tileop/gemm`: rename `GemmPy` → `Gemm`, register as `tl.Gemm`, rename FFI callbacks `tl.gemm_py.{lower, infer_layout}` → `tl.gemm.{lower, infer_layout}`, `_ffi_api.GemmPyGemmInst` → `GemmGetGemmInst`.\n- `tilelang/language/gemm_op.py`: delete `gemm_v1` / `gemm_v2` wrappers. `gemm()` now emits `tl.tileop.gemm` directly; `wgmma_gemm` / `tcgen05_gemm` drop the `_py` suffix.\n- `tilelang/env.py`: remove `TILELANG_USE_GEMM_V1` and the `use_gemm_v1()` helper.\n- `tilelang/ir.py`: drop the empty v1-era \\`class Gemm(Node, Scriptable): ...\\` placeholder that was colliding with the real \\`tileop.gemm.Gemm\\` wrapper under the \\`tl.Gemm\\` FFI type key (this collision was the only non-trivial bug surfaced by the smoke test).\n- `tilelang/contrib/cutedsl`: delete `cutedsl/gemm_v1.py` (runtime helper for the v1 cutedsl lowering path) and its re-export in `cutedsl/__init__.py`.\n\n### Tests / maint\n- `testing/python/tilelibrary/test_tilelang_tilelibrary_gemm.py` switches from `T.gemm_v2` to `T.gemm`.\n- `testing/python/transform/test_tilelang_transform_inject_fence_proxy.py::test_lower_fence_proxy` is rewritten to exercise `tl.tl_gemm_sp` instead of the removed `tl.tl_gemm`, preserving the fence-proxy assertion.\n- Delete `maint/gemm_v2/` (v1-vs-v2 benchmarking scripts) and drop the v1-specific comment from `maint/scripts/run_local_ci_test.sh`.\n\n### Intentionally kept\n- C++ headers under `src/tl_templates/{cuda,hip,cpp}/gemm*.h` are left in place as reference implementations. They are no longer reachable from the generated code path since the only consumer (`tl_gemm` builtin) is gone, but keeping them avoids a large, hard-to-reverse deletion in the same PR. They can be cleaned up in a follow-up.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Full C++ build (`cmake --build . -j`) — 100% clean.\n- [x] Python import smoke test: `tilelang`, `T.gemm`, `T.wgmma_gemm`, `T.tcgen05_gemm` all resolve; `T.gemm_v1` / `T.gemm_v2` are gone as expected.\n- [x] End-to-end GEMM kernel (256×256×256 fp16, pipelined, 3 stages) compiles and matches PyTorch reference with `max abs diff == 0`.\n- [x] `testing/python/transform/test_tilelang_transform_inject_fence_proxy.py::test_lower_fence_proxy` passes after the rewrite.\n- [ ] Broader regression on `testing/python/tilelibrary/` and `testing/python/transform/` — recommend running CI.\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Breaking Changes**\n  * GEMM selection unified to a single entrypoint; legacy GEMM selectors and the env var for choosing them removed. Public GEMM IR/object identity updated.\n\n* **Bug Fixes**\n  * Fixed multi-dimensional buffer indexing in MFMA paths.\n\n* **Documentation**\n  * Updated sparse GEMM docs to clarify lowering behavior.\n\n* **Chores**\n  * Removed legacy correctness tests and latency benchmarks; adjusted backend defaults and test decorators to require CUDA where applicable.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
